Pour espresso into a mug; stir in marshmallow topping, sugar, and cocoa powder until well blended. Heat milk in a saucepan over medium-low heat until lightly boiling, 3 to 5 minutes; remove from heat and froth milk with a frothing wand or a whisk. Pour frothed milk over espresso mixture. Top latte with whipped cream and graham cracker crumbs.